<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="NAME"
>NAME <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>podchecker - check the syntax of POD format documentation files</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="SYNOPSIS"
>SYNOPSIS <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p><b>podchecker</b> [<b>-help</b>] [<b>-man</b>] [<b>-(no)warnings</b>] [<i>file</i>&#160;...]</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="OPTIONS_AND_ARGUMENTS"
>OPTIONS AND ARGUMENTS <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<dl>
<dt><a name='help'></a><a name="-help"
><b>-help</b></a></dt>

<dd>
<p>Print a brief help message and exit.</p>

<dt><a name='man'></a><a name="-man"
><b>-man</b></a></dt>

<dd>
<p>Print the manual page and exit.</p>

<dt><a name='warnings'></a><a name="-warnings_-nowarnings"
><b>-warnings</b> <b>-nowarnings</b></a></dt>

<dd>
<p>Turn on/off printing of warnings.
Repeating <b>-warnings</b> increases the warning level,
i.e.
more warnings are printed.
Currently increasing to level two causes flagging of unescaped &#34;&#60;,&#62;&#34; characters.</p>

<dt><a name="file"
><i>file</i></a></dt>

<dd>
<p>The pathname of a POD file to syntax-check (defaults to standard input).</p>
</dd>
</dl>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="DESCRIPTION"
>DESCRIPTION <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p><b>podchecker</b> will read the given input files looking for POD syntax errors in the POD documentation and will print any errors it find to STDERR.
At the end,
it will print a status message indicating the number of errors found.</p>

<p>Directories are ignored,
an appropriate warning message is printed.</p>

<p><b>podchecker</b> invokes the <b>podchecker()</b> function exported by <b>Pod::Checker</b> Please see <a href="/~jhi/perl-5.8.1/lib/Pod/Checker.pm#podchecker()" class="podlinkpod"
>&#34;podchecker()&#34; in Pod::Checker</a> for more details.</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="RETURN_VALUE"
>RETURN VALUE <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p><b>podchecker</b> returns a 0 (zero) exit status if all specified POD files are ok.</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="ERRORS"
>ERRORS <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p><b>podchecker</b> returns the exit status 1 if at least one of the given POD files has syntax errors.</p>

<p>The status 2 indicates that at least one of the specified files does not contain <i>any</i> POD commands.</p>

<p>Status 1 overrides status 2.
If you want unambigouus results,
call <b>podchecker</b> with one single argument only.</p>

